events.name: New York Knicks at Indiana Pacers

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis scored a career-high 32 points and Victor Oladipo added 16 of his 22 in the second half Wednesday, leading the Indiana Pacers to a 121-107 opening victory over the New York Knicks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis, Oladipo lead Pacers past Knicks on opening night

headlines.description: — Evan Fournier gave Orlando the lead with a late 3-pointer, converted a three-point play in the final minute and scored 25 points in the Magic's 113-107 victory over the Miami Heat on Wednesday night in the opener for both teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Fournier has late surge, helps Magic beat Heat 113-107

headlines.description: — Joel Embiid scored the go-ahead basket with 1:09 left and had 29 points and 14 rebounds to lead the Philadelphia 76ers to a 113-107 win over Washington on Wednesday night and spoil Russell Westbrook’s triple-double Wizards' debut.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid leads 76ers past Westbrook, Wizards 113-107 in opener

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum banked in a fallaway, go-ahead 3-pointer in the final second, and Giannis Antetokounmpo missed the potential tying free throw with 0.4 seconds left, allowing the Boston Celtics to escape with a 122-121 victory over the Milwaukee Bucks...
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum hits big 3 to help Celtics beat Giannis, Bucks 122-121

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — JJ Redick converted a four-point play with just over a minute remaining and finished with 23 points, and Brandon Ingram led all scorers with 24 points as the New Orleans Pelicans rallied from an 11-point deficit and beat the relocated Toronto...
headlines.shortLinkText: Pelicans beat relocated Raptors 113-99; Van Gundy wins debut

headlines.description: — Trae Young scored 37 points and the revamped Atlanta Hawks pounded Chicago 124-104 on Wednesday night, spoiling Billy Donovan's debut as Bulls coach.
headlines.shortLinkText: Young scores 37 as Hawks pound Bulls 124-104 in opener

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Houston Rockets
San Antonio Spurs at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan had 28 points and nine assists, Dejounte Murray added 21 points as the San Antonio Spurs used a balanced attack to defeat the Memphis Grizzlies 131-119 on Wednesday night, overcoming a huge game by Ja Morant.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeRozan leads Spurs past Grizzlies as Morant has 42 points

headlines.description: — Malik Beasley scored 23 points and Karl-Anthony Towns had 22 points, 11 rebounds and seven assists, leading the Minnesota Timberwolves' rally to beat the Detroit Pistons 111-101 on Wednesday night in the season opener.
headlines.shortLinkText: Beasley, Towns lead T-wolves rally past Pistons 111-101

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield tipped in Harrison Barnes’ miss at the buzzer, lifting the Sacramento Kings to a stunning 124-122 win over the Denver Nuggets in overtime Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Hield tip-in leads Kings to 124-122 overtime win in Denver

events.name: Utah Jazz at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert had 20 points and 17 rebounds in a dominant season-opening performance, leading the Utah Jazz to a 120-100 victory over the Portland Trail Blazers on Wednesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gobert dominant inside, Lillard struggles, Jazz rout Blazers
